The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, July 28: Tata Tea has suffered a consolidated loss of Rs 19.57 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, 2009 compared with a profit of Rs 75.69 crore in the corresponding period last year. Consolidated total operating income of the company stood at Rs 1,295.60 crore compared with Rs 1,117.45 crore in the year-ago period.                             
	 Calcutta, July 28: Magma Fincorp aims to enter the non-life insurance segment. The company today announced a joint venture with German insurer HDI Gerling International Holding AG to tap the domestic general insurance market. Magma will hold 74 per cent equity in the JV company and HDI Gerling will have 26 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, July 28: Emami has posted a 35.1 per cent rise in its consolidated profit after tax at Rs 14.89 crore in the quarter ended June 30, 2009, over the year-ago period.                             
	 Calcutta, July 28: Birla Corporation Ltd has recorded a 69 per cent rise in its net profit at Rs 155.34 crore for the first quarter of 2009-10, over the corresponding period last fiscal. Harsh Lodha today moved Calcutta High Court challenging a Company Law Board order.                                                                                                                           
